BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique issued by the Chief of General Staff of FALA in </F>
Huambo; date not given] 
  [Text] 1. The General Staff of the Armed Forces for the 
Liberation of Angola [FALA] would like to vehemently deny that 
it is responsible for the suspension of humanitarian aid 
flights, as pointed out by Mrs. Mercedes Sayagues, World Food 
Program [WFP] representative for southern Africa. Humanitarian 
aid flights were canceled by the Popular Movement for the 
Liberation of Angola-Labor Party [MPLA-PT] government with the 
WFP's deliberate complicity. 
  2. The FALA General Staff would like to clarify that Huambo 
remains open for any humanitarian assistance. This assistance 
can be sent by air or by land as is most convenient for the 
involved organizations. 
  3. The FALA General Staff does not understand and does not 
want to understand that humanitarian assistance [words 
indistinct]. 
  4. The FALA General Staff would like to guarantee in its 
areas the freedom of flights and land movement [words 
indistinct]. 
  5. UNITA [words indistinct] to recolonize our country [words 
indistinct] the MPLA-PT government, particularly children and 
women [words indistinct]. 
  6. UNITA's reaction [words indistinct] the special 
representative of the UN secretary general [words indistinct]. 
  [Issued] [Words indistinct] June 1994 
  [Signed] Army General Arlindo Chenda Isaac Pena Ben-Ben, 
FALA 
chief of the General Staff. 

